===Etymology 2===
From {{inh|en|enm|caren}}, {{m|enm|carien}}, from {{inh|en|ang|carian|t=to sorrow, grieve, be troubled, be anxious, to care for, heed}}, from {{inh|en|gmw-pro|*karōn|t=to care}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*karōną|t=to care}}.

Cognate with {{cog|gmh|karn|t=to complain, lament, grieve, mourn}}, {{cog|gsw|karen}}, {{m|gsw|kären|t=to groan, wheeze, give a death rattle}}, {{cog|sv|kära|t=to fall in love}}, {{cog|is|kæra|t=to care, like}}, {{cog|got|𐌺𐌰𐍂𐍉𐌽|t=to be concerned}}.

